#12125 and friends appear to be caused by address space exhaustion between loading one giant pile of data and disposing the last.  Compacting the large object heap may help mitigate this.

https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.runtime.gcsettings.largeobjectheapcompactionmode(v=vs.110).aspx

```
GCSettings.LargeObjectHeapCompactionMode = GCLargeObjectHeapCompactionMode.CompactOnce;
GC.Collect();
```
